Wash and dry produce. Dice @tomato{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups} (2 1⁄4 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and @chili powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Season with salt and pepper. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

> PRO TIP: Swap sour cream for Greek yogurt for an even more gut-friendly option.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Lower heat and add a splash of water if veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

Heat another drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Add chicken in a single layer and season with @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} and remaining chili powder. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and a splash of water; cook until saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%TBSP} and lime zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with chicken and veggies. Drizzle with crema. Top with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup} and pico de gallo. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} and remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.
